# System and Network Information

## Lab Overview
Using fundamental commands to present System and Network data

## Objectives

- Understand the different types of information that displayed through these commands
- Identify the information that will be critical for diagnosing network health
- Learn how these Powershell capabilities are used to maintain/increase the security of networks


## Key Concepts

| Get-Computer-Info | displays detailed informatoin about the computer and OS |
| Get-LocalUser | shows the local user accounts on a computer. Provides such things as account names, descriptions and last password set time | 
| Get-NetIPConfiguration | shows the computer's network IP configuration. Lists information such as IP address, default gateway and DNS Server. similar to ipconfig in CLI |
| Get-NetIPAddress | shows the IP address assigned to network interfaces on the system. Focuses on the IPv4 and IPv6 address |
| WindowsBuildLabEx | property in Powershell. Lists build number(Windows 10,11), branch/lab infor and internal Microsoft build label |
| WindowsCurrentVersion | property of Get-ComputerInfo cmdlet. Shows the system current version info: Windows version, OSVersion, OSbuildnumber |
| WindowsEditionID |  details 'the edition of Windows isntalled on a machine, such as: Professional, Core, Enterprise, Education or Server |
| WindowsInstalltionType | details the kind of Windows Installation a system is using. Whether the system is a Client or Server |
| WindowsInstallDateFromRegistry | reports the date Windows was installed/re-installed/taken from the Windows registry |
| WindowsProductID | identifier for the installed Windows product, as recorded in the registry |
| WindowsProductName | Human-readable Windows name, such as: Windows 11 Pro or Windows 10 Enterprise |
| Administrator | built-in local admin account on Windows. Has elevated privileges compared to normal user |
| DefaultAccount | built-in local Windows account. System-managed account called DSMA(Default System Managed Account). Used for processes that are user-neutral or mult-user aware. Disabled by default |
| WDAGUtilityAccount | built-in local Windows System account tied to Microsoft Defender Application Gaurd. Disabled by default, uless Application Guard is enabled. Used to sign into Application Guard container |
| InterfaceAlias | Alias/name for a network interface, such as: Wi-Fi or Ethernet |
| InfterfaceIndex | numeric index identifier for a network interface |
| Netprofile.Name | 'Name' property inside the 'NetProfile' portion of Get-NetIPConfiguration output. Network connectoin profile name associated with the adapter.
| AddressFamily | details which IP version an address belongs to IPv4 or IPv6 |
| Type | IP address type(for a NetIPAddress object). Either Unicast or Anycast. Default is Unicast. Unicast is assigned to one interface/host. Anycast address can be assigned to multipe possible receivers |
| Prefixlength | subnet mask(written as a slash number). Specifies the subnet mask for an IP address.
| PrefixOrigin | details where the network subnet/prefix for an IP address comes. Whether thhe IP address was manually configured, DHCP, Router Advertised, built-in or other source |
| SuffixOrigin | details where the host portion of an IP address comes from. Valued from(0-5) similar to PrefixOrigin | 
| AddressState | states the current usability state of an IP address. Whether Invalid, Tentative, Duplicate, Deprecated, Preferred |
| ValidLifetime | states the length of time an IP address will remain valid |
| PreferredLifetime | sates the length of time an IP address will be 'preferred for new connections'. The address may still be valid, just not the preferred |
| SkipAsSource | true/false property. States whether an IP address shoudl be used as a source address for outgoing traffic. If True, the address will NOT be used for outgoing traffic and not be registered in DNS |
| PolicyStore | states which Window Policy/configuration store an IP setting is associated with. Whether ActiveStore(setting is active) or PersistentStore(settings are saved to survive restart) |

