### Syntax: Get-NetIPConfiguration

PS C:\Users\captain> Get-NetIPConfiguration

InterfaceAlias       : Ethernet
InterfaceIndex       : 5
InterfaceDescription : Amazon Elastic Network Adapter
NetProfile.Name      : Network 3
IPv4Address          : 10.10.178.209
IPv6DefaultGateway   :
IPv4DefaultGateway   : 10.10.0.1
DNSServer            : 10.0.0.2

- Server is using an Ethernet Adapter
- machine is using an Amazon virtual network adapter(running in AWS/Amazon EC2)
- if server wants to reach systems outside its subnet it sends traffic to 10.10.0.1

