## Security Relevance
- the cmdlets allow me to identify hosts
- Get-Computerinfo is the main tool for identifying hosts and gaining system context.
- Get-LocalUser can be used for overall account review and checking which accounts have privileged access
- networking cmdlets can be focused to reduce noise by piping these cmdlets through others such as Where-Object, Sort-Object and Select-Object
